<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-14T15:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-14T15:40:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1154.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-14T16:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your April 11, 11 a.m. The Receivership has been instructed to advance
                            $3,500 per diem instead of the $2,000 already arranged for. This sum
                            will be advanced for a period of fifteen days. It is expected from your
                            reports that a longer campaign will not be necessary. Unless Congress
                            approves proposition for loan before period of fifteen days is passed
                            all available funds will be exhausted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>